title: 16 Cheyne Walk
description:
Built in 1717.Formerly known as Tudor House &  Queen's House.It has had several notable residents:

Dante Gabriel Rossetti (1828-1882).English Pre-Raphaelite (co-founder) Artist.Lived here from 1862 to 1882.

The 4 following people all lived here during Rossetti's residency.

Algernon Charles Swinburne (1837-1909).English Poet.Lived here.1862 to 1872.
Share a Blue Plaque with Dante Gabriel Rossetti..

George Meredith (1828-1909).English Novelist.Lived here.1862 to 1864

Sir Hall Caine (1853-1931).'Manx' Novelist,Playwright.Lived here.1881 to 1882.

Frederick Sandys (1829-1904).English Artist.Lived here.1861-1862

Mortimer Menpes (1855-1938).Australian Artist.Lived here.

-----

Jacques Blumenthal (1829-1908).German Pianist,tutor to the Royal Family.Lived and Died here in 1908

Sir John Paul Getty Jnr (II)(1932-2003).Anglo-American Philanthropist.Lived here.1970's-1990's.

title: Lost Theatre
description:
LOST is a vibrant and exciting company with a proven 30 year track record of helping young arts professionals to make the most of their talents. We produce shows, Festivals and classes so there’s something here for everyone – whether you have recently left training and are looking for somewhere to showcase your talents, want to sharpen up you audition technique before applying to drama schools or simply wish to have a go at acting, LOST offers something for you.
Each year LOST present 9 plays directed by respected industry professional open to anyone 27 years or under. These are produced to a high standard and are the perfect show case for agents to come and see you. We have two other groups that focus on people under 21 and under 16. We run 3 Festivals that encourage new writers and directors to stretch their talents. Our One Act Festival is the perfect vehicle for writers to showcase new plays and receive instant feedback from our Adjudicator. The 5 Minute Festival looks at short form work and asks the question “What can you do in 300 seconds?” – it’s quite a challenge. Finally, the Bedtime Festival looks into the world of children’s stories and drama.
Alongside all this there are our classes and occasional question and answer sessions with well known actors.
